Don't know if someone has already written/prompted a story like this but here goes nothing...

>Futuristic setting
>Anon works at scrap yard
>one day his job is to salvage any valuable components from a deactivated female android (androids in this setting have been around for 3 decades and are very common in upper middle class houses and above, mostly as servants) that was found just thrown away as garbage in some rich area
>as Anon is trying to disassemble her, he accidentally reboots her back online
>after calming down the scared android and explaining where she is, she tells Anon that she had been bought by a rich family as a homeschool teacher and 24/7 friend for their daughter
>when their daughter became old enough, they decided they no longer needed the android, deactivated her and threw her away
>After telling her story, Anon (him being a friendless loser and her having nowhere else to go, takes her to his modest low-rent apartment (somehow) in secret, since stealing company property is grounds for firing
>???

For worldbuilding, androids have been around for like 30 years or so, the first androids being developed solely for warfare but due to some complications never went up, then they were developed and sold as household property. The android Anon met would maybe be the 3rd versions of the androids, them being fully customizable. In my head I pictured the android to be based on the young daughter's favorite animal cartoon/movie character, so the android would probably be very colorful (like the animatronics from FNAF)
